net.openhft.chronicle.core.analytics

Interface AnalyticsFacade


  • public interface AnalyticsFacade
    Provides means for libraries to report analytics to an upstream receiver.

    Analytics instances only provides a best-effort to propagate events to the upstream receiver.

    Analytics can be turned off buy setting the system property "chronicle.analytics.disable=true" prior to acquiring any Analytics instances.

      • sendEvent

        default void sendEvent(@NotNull
                       @NotNull String name)
        Sends an event to Google Analytics as identified by the provided event name.

        Depending on settings and other conditions, the event may or may not be sent upstream. For example, some implementations may send a limited number of upstream events per time unit.

      • sendEvent

        void sendEvent(@NotNull
               @NotNull String name,
               @NotNull
               @NotNull Map<String,String> additionalEventParameters)
        Sends an event to Google Analytics as identified by the provided event name including the provided additionalEventParameters in the event.

        Depending on settings and other conditions, the event may or may not be sent upstream. For example, some implementations may send a limited number of upstream events per time unit.

      • builder

        @NotNull
static @NotNull AnalyticsFacade.Builder builder(@NotNull
                                                         @NotNull String measurementId,
                                                         @NotNull
                                                         @NotNull String apiSecret)
        Creates and returns a new empty Builder that can be used to create an Analytic instance.

        The builder can only create one single Analytic instance.

        If isEnabled() returns false, then a NOP builder is returned.

        Parameters:
        measurementId - to use for reporting
        apiSecret - to use for reporting
        Returns:
        a new empty Builder that can be used to create an Analytic instance
